---
// input: siteConfig data, related guides list layout component
// output: Upgrades guide page showing progression prioritizations and defense locks
// pos: src/pages/upgrades.astro (更新规则：文件变更需同步本注释与所属目录 README)

import SiteLayout from "../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";
import RelatedGuides from "../components/RelatedGuides.astro";
import { siteConfig } from "../data/config";
---

<SiteLayout title="Merge a Nuke Guide Upgrades | Roblox Tycoon Order" description="Optimize your base builds with the Merge a Nuke guide upgrades path. Prioritize spawn speed, hangar expansion, and base lock shield levels.">
  <main class="content-page">
    <section class="prose-block" style="margin-bottom: 40px;">
      <p class="eyebrow">Upgrades guide</p>
      <h1>{siteConfig.gameName} Upgrades Guide</h1>
      <p>Deciding where to spend your cash in Roblox Merge a Nuke can make the difference between a stalled tycoon and a rapid rebirth setup. This page provides a clear upgrade roadmap, prioritizing attributes that keep your merge engine running efficiently while defending your hard-earned cash.</p>
      
      <div style="margin-top: 24px; padding: 20px; background: rgba(234, 179, 8, 0.05); border: 1.5px solid rgba(234, 179, 8, 0.15); border-radius: var(--radius-interactive); line-height: 1.6;">
        <h3 style="color: var(--accent); margin-bottom: 8px;">Upgrade Strategy Rationale</h3>
        <p style="margin-bottom: 0; font-size: 0.9rem;">
          Not all base upgrades are created equal. Spending early-game currency on PvP stats like nuke health or raid cooldown reduction yields poor progression gains. This <strong>Merge a Nuke guide</strong> teaches you how to prioritize spawn flow and hangar storage to compound your economic strength first.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section" aria-labelledby="upgrade-prioritization" style="margin-bottom: 48px;">
      <p class="eyebrow">Priority order</p>
      <h2 id="upgrade-prioritization" style="margin-bottom: 24px;">Attributes upgrade prioritization</h2>
      <p style="margin-bottom: 24px; line-height: 1.6;">Your primary investment focus should always be your economic engine. By spending cash on attributes that reduce the manual merging effort, you unlock top-tier weapons faster and with less board friction.</p>

      <div class="card-grid">
        <article class="card" style="border-radius: var(--radius-card); border-color: var(--line);">
          <h3 style="color: var(--color-yellow); margin-bottom: 12px; font-size: 1.1rem; font-family: var(--font-display);">Improving spawn flow first</h3>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 12px; font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.5;">Spawn level and spawn rate upgrades are the most critical purchases in early tycoon stages. Increasing these attributes allows you to spawn higher starting tiers (such as spawning tier-2 or tier-3 bombs directly) and pings new pieces faster. This <strong>Merge a Nuke guide</strong> highlights that directly spawning tier-3 items saves you dozens of manual merges.</p>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 0; font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.5;">Reinvesting your cash here minimizes board crowding. Spawning higher-tier items instantly frees up grid workspace, keeping your merge chains running smoothly without requiring a completely clean board.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card" style="border-radius: var(--radius-card); border-color: var(--line);">
          <h3 style="color: var(--color-yellow); margin-bottom: 12px; font-size: 1.1rem; font-family: var(--font-display);">Upgrading hangar capacity</h3>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 12px; font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.5;">Hangar slots determine how many active weapons can generate passive cash simultaneously. If you have high-tier weapons but no open hangar slots, your idle income rate will stall. Upgrading hangar capacity ensures that every new merge tier actively contributes to your cash flow.</p>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 0; font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.5;">This <strong>Merge a Nuke guide</strong> recommends keeping your hangar upgrades aligned with your spawn tier capacity. A balanced base layout ensures that your cash-per-minute rate scales linearly as you unlock advanced nuclear warheads.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section grid-section" aria-labelledby="defense-upgrades" style="margin-bottom: 48px;">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Defense & Raid</p>
        <h2 id="defense-upgrades">Defense and raid enhancements</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="card-grid">
        <article class="card" style="border-radius: var(--radius-card); border-color: var(--line);">
          <h3 style="color: var(--accent);">Upgrading locking shield duration</h3>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 12px; font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.5;">Base lock shield upgrades are essential for protecting offline cash. The base shield blocks opponent raids, but it has a limited duration before it requires a cooldown. Investing in shield duration keeps your island safe for longer periods while you are away.</p>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 12px; font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.5;">This <strong>Merge a Nuke guide</strong> advises upgrading your locking shield duration before leaving the server. A long-lasting shield ensures that your passive hangar income accumulates safely, preventing opponents from stealing progress while you are offline.</p>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 0; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--muted);">Longer shield duration secures offline progress during away-from-keyboard windows.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card" style="border-radius: var(--radius-card); border-color: var(--line);">
          <h3 style="color: var(--accent);">PVP raid weapon multipliers</h3>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 12px; font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.5;">Raid attributes, such as weapon blast radius and raid reload cooldowns, are luxury late-game upgrades. These attributes increase the cash siphoned from opponent bases during active raids. However, they do not boost your passive economic engine.</p>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 12px; font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.5;">Only spend cash on raid attributes when your passive income rate is stable enough to easily cover target upgrade gaps. This <strong>Merge a Nuke guide</strong> suggests holding off on heavy raid upgrades until you are preparing for high-multiplier rebirth runs.</p>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 0; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--muted);">Upgrade raid parameters only after your passive income rate has reached stable late-game levels.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <RelatedGuides currentSlug="upgrades" />
  </main>
</SiteLayout>
